{'problem_id': 'op_000013', 'moved_to': 'solved', 'target_row': {'id': 'op_000013', 'stmt': 'вҲғ (Оұ : Type*), ACR Оұ вҲ§ ACR.Prov Оұ вҲ§ ACR.Reft Оұ вҲ§ ACR.APS Оұ вҲ§ ACR.C5 Оұ вҲ§ Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ) вҲ§ В¬ Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ)', 'src': 'expand', 'mode': 'expand_candidate', 'summary_delta': 'Now that GГ¶del fixed points are canonical up to equivalence, the most informative outward step is a strict separation question against Henkin existence rather than more local normalization. A counterexample of this form would sharply resolve whether the remaining Henkin/GГ¶del bridge should be pursued as an equivalence theorem or as a separation boundary, directly advancing a major stated bottleneck.', 'source_kind': 'expand_candidate', 'generated_from_source_id': 'op_000001', 'generated_from_source_kind': 'open_problem', 'priority': 'medium', 'priority_rationale': 'A Henkin-without-Godel counterexample would decisively separate the two existence notions, but it is a single boundary example rather than a reusable criterion.', 'failure_count': 0, 'parent_problem_ids': []}, 'solved_row': {'id': 'op_000013', 'stmt': 'вҲғ (Оұ : Type*), ACR Оұ вҲ§ ACR.Prov Оұ вҲ§ ACR.Reft Оұ вҲ§ ACR.APS Оұ вҲ§ ACR.C5 Оұ вҲ§ Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ) вҲ§ В¬ Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ)', 'thm': 'thm_henkin_without_godel_model_000013', 'run_id': '20260414-221630-loop', 'iteration': 8, 'session_type': 'loop'}, 'counterexample_row': None, 'duplicate_stmt_rows_removed': [], 'current_iteration': 8, 'picked_problem_id': 'op_000013', 'picked_problem_priority': 'high', 'result': 'proof', 'verify_success': True, 'verify_error_excerpt': '', 'original_stmt': 'вҲғ (Оұ : Type*), ACR Оұ вҲ§ ACR.Prov Оұ вҲ§ ACR.Reft Оұ вҲ§ ACR.APS Оұ вҲ§ ACR.C5 Оұ вҲ§ Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ) вҲ§ В¬ Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ)', 'statement_prelude_code': '', 'formalized_stmt': 'вҲғ (Оұ : Type*) (_ : ACR Оұ) (_ : ACR.Prov Оұ) (_ : ACR.Reft Оұ) (_ : ACR.APS Оұ) (_ : ACR.C5 Оұ), Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ) вҲ§ В¬ Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ)', 'prelude_code': 'inductive Two where\n  | ff\n  | tt\nderiving DecidableEq\n\ninstance : LE Two where\n  le x y := match x, y with\n    | .ff, _ => True\n    | .tt, .tt => True\n    | .tt, .ff => False\n\ninstance : Top Two where\n  top := .tt\n\ninstance : Bot Two where\n  bot := .ff\n\ninstance : Preorder Two where\n  le := (В· вүӨ В·)\n  le_refl := by\n    intro x\n    cases x <;> trivial\n  le_trans := by\n    intro a b c hab hbc\n    cases a <;> cases b <;> cases c <;> trivial\n\ninstance : ACR (ULift Two) where\n  toTop := ULift.instTop\n  toBot := ULift.instBot\n  toPreorder := ULift.instPreorder\n\ninstance : ACR.Prov (ULift Two) where\n  prov := id\n\ninstance : ACR.Reft (ULift Two) where\n  reft x := match x.down with\n    | .ff => вҹЁ.ttвҹ©\n    | .tt => вҹЁ.ffвҹ©\n\ninstance : ACR.APS (ULift Two) where\n  prov_mono := by\n    intro x y h\n    simpa using h\n  reft_anti_mono := by\n    intro x y h\n    cases x using ULift.casesOn with\n    | _ x =>\n      cases y using ULift.casesOn with\n      | _ y =>\n        cases x <;> cases y <;> trivial\n  top_le_reft_bot := by\n    trivial\n  le_reft_top_of_le_prov_of_le_reft := by\n    intro x y hxy hxr\n    cases x using ULift.casesOn with\n    | _ x =>\n      cases y using ULift.casesOn with\n      | _ y =>\n        cases x <;> cases y <;> trivial\n  reft_le_prov_reft := by\n    intro x\n    cases x using ULift.casesOn with\n    | _ x =>\n      cases x <;> trivial\n\ninstance : ACR.C5 (ULift Two) where\n  le_top := by\n    intro x\n    cases x using ULift.casesOn with\n    | _ x =>\n      cases x <;> trivial', 'prover_statement_result': 'ok', 'prover_attempts_used': 1, 'priority_refresh_ran': True, 'priority_refresh_error': '', 'expand_candidates': [{'statement': 'вҲҖ {Оұ : Type*} [ACR Оұ] [ACR.Prov Оұ] [ACR.Reft Оұ] [ACR.APS Оұ] [ACR.C5 Оұ], Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ) вҶ’ Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ)', 'rationale': 'The solved example already shows that Henkin existence does not force GГ¶del existence, so the remaining summary-level comparison question is whether GГ¶del existence is strictly stronger or whether the two notions are genuinely incomparable. This implication is the cleanest core statement for deciding that boundary.'}, {'statement': 'вҲҖ {Оұ : Type*} [ACR Оұ] [ACR.Prov Оұ] [ACR.Reft Оұ] [ACR.APS Оұ] [ACR.C5 Оұ], Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ) вҶ’ В¬ ((вҠ (вҠӨ : Оұ)) вүӨ вҠҘ)', 'rationale': 'This sharpens the current provability-side bridge by testing whether consistency is actually needed to rule out refutability of `вҠ вҠӨ`. Resolving it would directly advance the stated bottleneck of turning the modal existence theorem into a condition expressed purely at the level of `вҠ вҠӨ`.'}, {'statement': 'Any two-element linearly ordered instance of `ACR + Prov + Reft + APS + C5` with `в–Ў = id` and `вҠ вҠҘ = вҠӨ`, `вҠ вҠӨ = вҠҘ` satisfies `Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ) вҲ§ В¬ Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ)`', 'rationale': 'The verified proof used one concrete two-point model; abstracting that witness into a reusable schema would turn a single example into a counterexample-construction principle. That is valuable beyond the present theorem because it gives a controlled mechanism for future separation and threshold arguments rather than another isolated existential witness.'}], 'stored_expand_rows': [{'id': 'op_000014', 'stmt': 'вҲҖ {Оұ : Type*} [ACR Оұ] [ACR.Prov Оұ] [ACR.Reft Оұ] [ACR.APS Оұ] [ACR.C5 Оұ], Nonempty (ACR.GГ¶delFixpoint Оұ) вҶ’ Nonempty (ACR.HenkinFixpoint Оұ)', 'src': 'expand', 'mode': 'expand_candidate', 'summary_delta': 'The solved example already shows that Henkin existence does not force GГ¶del existence, so the remaining summary-level comparison question is whether GГ¶del existence is strictly stronger or whether the two notions are genuinely incomparable. This implication is the cleanest core statement for deciding that boundary.', 'source_kind': 'expand_can